<!--DOCTYPE section SYSTEM "file:/usr/share/sgml/db42xml/docbookx.dtd"--><ns2589:section xmlns:ns2589="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.kernel.architecture.virtualFileSystem">

  <ns2590:title xmlns:ns2590="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The virtual file system</ns2590:title>
  <ns2591:para xmlns:ns2591="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Linux supports a very wide range of physical and logical file systems. This allows Linux
    to interact easily and effectively with a large number of systems including
    other operating systems.
  </ns2591:para>
  <ns2592:para xmlns:ns2592="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The design of the <ns2593:emphasis xmlns:ns2593="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">virtual file system</ns2593:emphasis> is discussed in
    <ns2594:xref xmlns:ns2594="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.platforms.linux.fileSystem.genericStructure"/>.
  </ns2592:para>  
  
</ns2589:section>